.TH _PRINTF 1 "21 juillet 2025" "1.0" "First page of _printf manual"


.SH NAME

\fB_printf\fR -  function that produces output according to a format.


.SH SYNOPSIS

.B	int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION

The \fB_printf\fR function prints a formatted string to the standard ouput (stdout).
It takes a format string and a variable number of arguments.

.PP
.B Supported format specifiers are:

- %c: character.
- %s: string.
- %i/%d: signed decimal integer.
- %%: the percent character.

.SH RETURN VALUES

The function returns the total number of characters printed to the standard output.
In case of error, a negative value may be returned: return (-1);

.SH EXAMPLES

Here is a simple example of using
.B _printf
In a C program: print a the string "bisous" followed by a newline:

.nf
#include <stdio.h>

int main (void) {
	_printf("bisous \\n");
	return (0);
}
.fi

